{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52ba1243-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1741"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1741"},"text":"§ 1741.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Foreign official documents","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"An official record or document of a foreign country may be evidenced by a copy, summary, or excerpt authenticated as provided in the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52ba1244-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 646","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/948"},"text":"62 Stat. 948","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-05-24/ch139/s92/b"},"text":"May 24, 1949, ch. 139, § 92(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/103"},"text":"63 Stat. 103","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/619/s5/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–619, § 5(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-10-03"},"text":"Oct. 3, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/996"},"text":"78 Stat. 996","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52ba1245-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id52ba1246-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id52ba1247-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"1948 ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Act","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 695e (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1936-06-20/ch640/s6"},"text":"June 20, 1936, ch. 640, § 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/1563"},"text":"49 Stat. 1563","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Words “Nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to alter, amend, or repeal ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s689"},"text":"section 689 of this title","children":[],"tail":",” at the end of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s695e"},"text":"section 695e of title 28","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., were omitted. Although significant in the original Act, such words are unnecessary in a revision wherein both sections in question, as revised, are enacted at the same time."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"See also Rule 44 of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s695e–1"},"text":"Section 695e–1 of title 28","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., providing for certification of Vatican City Documents will be incorporated in title 22, U.S.C., Foreign Relations and Intercourse."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Changes were made in phraseology.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id52ba1248-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"1949 ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Act","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section corrects a typographical error in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s1741"},"text":"section 1741 of title 28","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id52ba1249-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id52ba124a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1964—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/619"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–619","children":[],"tail":" substituted “An official record or document of a foreign country may be evidenced by a copy, summary, or excerpt authenticated as provided in the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure” for “A copy of any foreign document of record or on file in a public office of a foreign country or political subdivision thereof, certified by the lawful custodian thereof, shall be admissible in evidence when authenticated by a certificate of a consular officer of the United States resident in such foreign country, under the seal of his office, that the copy has been certified by the lawful custodian” in text, and “official documents” for “documents, generally; copies” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1949—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1949","children":[],"tail":", corrected spelling of “admissible”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
